    "gradient-based estimator.",
    "For example, Hammoudeh and Lowd (2022) observe that renormalized TracInCP, which they term gradient aggregated similarity (gas), is particularly effective at generating influence rankings.",
    "Hammoudeh and Lowd (2022) also provide a renormalized version of influence functions, Since renormalized influence functions do not require estimating additional HVPs, it is considerably faster than RelatIF.",
    "Renormalized influence functions also do not have the additional error associated with estimating RelatIF's additional HVPs, foot_18 This section should not be interpreted to mean that gradient magnitude is unimportant for influence analysis.",
    "On the contrary, gradient magnitude has a significant effect on training."
